Pam Golding Properties has listed a seven-bedroom 22,500 sqm estate for the mega-rich in the heart of Sandhurst, with a view of Sandton’s skyline. Designed by renowned architect Ian Gandini, the estate includes 7 bedrooms, 9 bathrooms, 9 reception rooms, and 5 garages. The property has excellent security with cameras, an electric fence, beams, and a 24-hour guardhouse. It includes a fully fitted library/ study with sliding doors allowing nature to form part of the living environment. The guest suite has its own lounge and separate entrance. The home features a gym with a steam shower, and for the wine connoisseur – an authentically designed red brick wine cellar with vaulted ceilings, and is temperature controlled with 5 separate rooms culminating in a wine tasting room, and kitchenette. The garden includes a pool room with a pub and change room facilities. Additional features: Staff accommodation – 5 bedroom suites, lounge, dining room, kitchen
Tennis court
2 boreholes. automated irrigation system
